# Optimization: Leveraging Layout Context for Gantt Data

This plan optimizes the Gantt chart by using the project list and workspace metadata already stored in the "Layout Context" (Sidebar memory), removing redundant server-side database calls and reducing the initial page load weight.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> -   **Prop Reduction**: I am removing `projects`, `tags`, and `permissions` from the `WorkspaceGanttClient` props. These will now be fetched directly from the `useWorkspaceLayout` hook.
> -   **Server-Side Leaner**: The `WorkspaceGanttView` (Server Component) will no longer fetch project lists or workspace tags, as these are already delivered by the structural layout shell.
> -   **Members exception**: Workspace-wide members will still be fetched as they are not currently part of the lightweight layout data.

